#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn55.40"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn55.40:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 55 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 55 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn55.40:0.2"
msgid "4. Puññābhisandavagga "
msgstr "4. Overflowing Merit "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 40. Nandiyasakkasutta → nandiyasuttaṃ (bj) | nandiya (pts1)
msgctxt "sn55.40:0.3"
msgid "40. Nandiyasakkasutta "
msgstr "40. Nandiya the Sakyan "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn55.40:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sakkesu viharati kapilavatthusmiṃ nigrodhārāme. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying in the land of the Sakyans, near Kapilavatthu in the Banyan Tree Monastery. "

msgctxt "sn55.40:1.2"
msgid "Atha kho nandiyo sakko yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho nandiyo sakko bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then Nandiya the Sakyan went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn55.40:1.3"
msgid "“yasseva nu kho, bhante, ariyasāvakassa cattāri sotāpattiyaṅgāni sabbena sabbaṃ sabbathā sabbaṃ natthi sveva nu kho, bhante, ariyasāvako pamādavihārī”ti. "
msgstr "“Sir, if a noble disciple were to totally and utterly lack the four factors of stream-entry, would they live negligently?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.398, sc2
msgctxt "sn55.40:2.1"
msgid "“‘Yassa kho, nandiya, cattāri sotāpattiyaṅgāni sabbena sabbaṃ sabbathā sabbaṃ natthi tamahaṃ bāhiro puthujjanapakkhe ṭhito’ti vadāmi. "
msgstr "“Nandiya, someone who totally and utterly lacks these four factors of stream-entry is an outsider who belongs with the ordinary persons, I say. "

msgctxt "sn55.40:2.2"
msgid "Api ca, nandiya, yathā ariyasāvako pamādavihārī ceva hoti, appamādavihārī ca "
msgstr "Neverthless, Nandiya, as to how a noble disciple lives negligently and how they live diligently, "

msgctxt "sn55.40:2.3"
msgid "taṃ suṇāhi, sādhukaṃ manasi karohi; bhāsissāmī”ti. "
msgstr "listen and attend closely, I will speak. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn55.40:2.4"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho nandiyo sakko bhagavato paccassosi. "
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” Nandiya replied. "

msgctxt "sn55.40:2.5"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca: "
msgstr "The Buddha said this: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn55.40:3.1"
msgid "“Kathañca, nandiya, ariyasāvako pamādavihārī hoti? "
msgstr "“And how does a noble disciple live negligently? "

msgctxt "sn55.40:3.2"
msgid "Idha, nandiya, ariyasāvako buddhe aveccappasādena samannāgato hoti—"
msgstr "Firstly, a noble disciple has experiential confidence in the Buddha … "

msgctxt "sn55.40:3.3"
msgid "itipi so bhagavā … pe … satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavāti. "
msgstr " "

#. VAR: uttari → uttariṃ (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "sn55.40:3.4"
msgid "So tena buddhe aveccappasādena santuṭṭho na uttari vāyamati divā pavivekāya, rattiṃ paṭisallānāya. "
msgstr "They’re content with that confidence, and don’t make a further effort for solitude by day or retreat by night. "

msgctxt "sn55.40:3.5"
msgid "Tassa evaṃ pamattassa viharato pāmojjaṃ na hoti. "
msgstr "When they live negligently, there’s no joy. "

msgctxt "sn55.40:3.6"
msgid "Pāmojje asati, pīti na hoti. "
msgstr "When there’s no joy, there’s no rapture. "

msgctxt "sn55.40:3.7"
msgid "Pītiyā asati, passaddhi na hoti. "
msgstr "When there’s no rapture, there’s no tranquility. "

msgctxt "sn55.40:3.8"
msgid "Passaddhiyā asati, dukkhaṃ viharati. "
msgstr "When there’s no tranquility, there’s suffering. "

msgctxt "sn55.40:3.9"
msgid "Dukkhino cittaṃ na samādhiyati. "
msgstr "When one is suffering, the mind does not become immersed in samādhi. "

msgctxt "sn55.40:3.10"
msgid "Asamāhite citte dhammā na pātubhavanti. "
msgstr "When the mind is not immersed in samādhi, principles do not become clear. "

msgctxt "sn55.40:3.11"
msgid "Dhammānaṃ apātubhāvā pamādavihārītveva saṅkhyaṃ gacchati. "
msgstr "Because principles have not become clear, they’re reckoned to live negligently. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn55.40:4.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, nandiya, ariyasāvako dhamme … pe … "
msgstr "Furthermore, a noble disciple has experiential confidence in the teaching … "

msgctxt "sn55.40:4.2"
msgid "saṅghe … pe … "
msgstr "the Saṅgha … "

msgctxt "sn55.40:4.3"
msgid "ariyakantehi sīlehi samannāgato hoti akhaṇḍehi … pe … samādhisaṃvattanikehi. "
msgstr "And they have the ethical conduct loved by the noble ones … leading to immersion. "

msgctxt "sn55.40:4.4"
msgid "So tehi ariyakantehi sīlehi santuṭṭho na uttari vāyamati divā pavivekāya rattiṃ paṭisallānāya. "
msgstr "They’re content with that ethical conduct loved by the noble ones, and don’t make a further effort for solitude by day or retreat by night. "

msgctxt "sn55.40:4.5"
msgid "Tassa evaṃ pamattassa viharato pāmojjaṃ na hoti. "
msgstr "When they live negligently, there’s no joy. "

msgctxt "sn55.40:4.6"
msgid "Pāmojje asati, pīti na hoti. "
msgstr "When there’s no joy, there’s no rapture. "

msgctxt "sn55.40:4.7"
msgid "Pītiyā asati, passaddhi na hoti. "
msgstr "When there’s no rapture, there’s no tranquility. "

msgctxt "sn55.40:4.8"
msgid "Passaddhiyā asati, dukkhaṃ viharati. "
msgstr "When there’s no tranquility, there’s suffering. "

msgctxt "sn55.40:4.9"
msgid "Dukkhino cittaṃ na samādhiyati. "
msgstr "When one is suffering, the mind does not become immersed in samādhi. "

msgctxt "sn55.40:4.10"
msgid "Asamāhite citte dhammā na pātubhavanti. "
msgstr "When the mind is not immersed in samādhi, principles do not become clear. "

msgctxt "sn55.40:4.11"
msgid "Dhammānaṃ apātubhāvā pamādavihārītveva saṅkhyaṃ gacchati. "
msgstr "Because principles have not become clear, they’re reckoned to live negligently. "

msgctxt "sn55.40:4.12"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, nandiya, ariyasāvako pamādavihārī hoti. "
msgstr "That’s how a noble disciple lives negligently. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.399, sc5
msgctxt "sn55.40:5.1"
msgid "Kathañca, nandiya, ariyasāvako appamādavihārī hoti? "
msgstr "And how does a noble disciple live diligently? "

msgctxt "sn55.40:5.2"
msgid "Idha, nandiya, ariyasāvako buddhe aveccappasādena samannāgato hoti—"
msgstr "Firstly, a noble disciple has experiential confidence in the Buddha … "

msgctxt "sn55.40:5.3"
msgid "itipi so bhagavā … pe … satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavāti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn55.40:5.4"
msgid "So tena buddhe aveccappasādena asantuṭṭho uttari vāyamati divā pavivekāya rattiṃ paṭisallānāya. "
msgstr "But they’re not content with that confidence, and make a further effort for solitude by day and retreat by night. "

msgctxt "sn55.40:5.5"
msgid "Tassa evaṃ appamattassa viharato pāmojjaṃ jāyati. "
msgstr "When they live diligently, joy springs up. "

msgctxt "sn55.40:5.6"
msgid "Pamuditassa pīti jāyati. "
msgstr "Being joyful, rapture springs up. "

msgctxt "sn55.40:5.7"
msgid "Pītimanassa kāyo passambhati. "
msgstr "When the mind is full of rapture, the body becomes tranquil. "

msgctxt "sn55.40:5.8"
msgid "Passaddhakāyo sukhaṃ vediyati. "
msgstr "When the body is tranquil, they feel bliss. "

msgctxt "sn55.40:5.9"
msgid "Sukhino cittaṃ samādhiyati. "
msgstr "And when blissful, the mind becomes immersed in samādhi. "

msgctxt "sn55.40:5.10"
msgid "Samāhite citte dhammā pātubhavanti. "
msgstr "When the mind is immersed in samādhi, principles become clear. "

msgctxt "sn55.40:5.11"
msgid "Dhammānaṃ pātubhāvā appamādavihārītveva saṅkhyaṃ gacchati. "
msgstr "Because principles have become clear, they’re reckoned to live diligently. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "sn55.40:6.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, nandiya, ariyasāvako dhamme … pe … "
msgstr "Furthermore, a noble disciple has experiential confidence in the teaching … "

msgctxt "sn55.40:6.2"
msgid "saṅghe … pe … "
msgstr "the Saṅgha … "

msgctxt "sn55.40:6.3"
msgid "ariyakantehi sīlehi samannāgato hoti akhaṇḍehi … pe … samādhisaṃvattanikehi. "
msgstr "And they have the ethical conduct loved by the noble ones … leading to immersion. "

msgctxt "sn55.40:6.4"
msgid "So tehi ariyakantehi sīlehi asantuṭṭho uttari vāyamati divā pavivekāya rattiṃ paṭisallānāya. "
msgstr "But they’re not content with that ethical conduct loved by the noble ones, and make a further effort for solitude by day and retreat by night. "

msgctxt "sn55.40:6.5"
msgid "Tassa evaṃ appamattassa viharato pāmojjaṃ jāyati. "
msgstr "When they live diligently, joy springs up. "

msgctxt "sn55.40:6.6"
msgid "Pamuditassa pīti jāyati. "
msgstr "Being joyful, rapture springs up. "

msgctxt "sn55.40:6.7"
msgid "Pītimanassa kāyo passambhati. "
msgstr "When the mind is full of rapture, the body becomes tranquil. "

msgctxt "sn55.40:6.8"
msgid "Passaddhakāyo sukhaṃ vediyati. "
msgstr "When the body is tranquil, they feel bliss. "

msgctxt "sn55.40:6.9"
msgid "Sukhino cittaṃ samādhiyati. "
msgstr "And when blissful, the mind becomes immersed in samādhi. "

msgctxt "sn55.40:6.10"
msgid "Samāhite citte dhammā pātubhavanti. "
msgstr "When the mind is immersed in samādhi, principles become clear. "

msgctxt "sn55.40:6.11"
msgid "Dhammānaṃ pātubhāvā appamādavihārītveva saṅkhyaṃ gacchati. "
msgstr "Because principles have become clear, they’re reckoned to live diligently. "

msgctxt "sn55.40:6.12"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, nandiya, ariyasāvako appamādavihārī hotī”ti. "
msgstr "That’s how a noble disciple lives diligently.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn55.40:6.13"
msgid "Dasamaṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn55.40:6.14"
msgid "Puññābhisandavaggo catuttho. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "sn55.40:7.1"
msgid "Abhisandā tayo vuttā, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn55.40:7.2"
msgid "duve devapadāni ca; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn55.40:7.3"
msgid "Sabhāgataṃ mahānāmo, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn55.40:7.4"
msgid "vassaṃ kāḷī ca nandiyāti. "
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p></blockquote></article></section></body></html>
